<section id="sect-00007">
<title>Adverse Effects and Contraindications</title>
<para id="para-00009">Typical adverse effects of histamine blockers include diarrhea, headaches, mental confusion, agitation, depression, <term id="term-00010">gynecomastia</term>, <term id="term-00011">neutropenia</term>, <term id="term-00012">agranulocytosis</term>, increases in serum <term id="term-00013">transaminase</term>, <term id="term-00014">arthralgia</term>, rash, and <term id="term-00015">alopecia</term>. In rare cases bradycardia, tachycardia, and AV heart block have been reported. Contraindications include hypersensitivity to the drug or any of its components.</para>
